"title": "7545: outsiders",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7545: outsiders",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Israel recognised two general categories of outsiders: those who lived outside Israel, usually referred to as “the nations” or “the Gentiles”, and foreigners resident within Israel's boundaries. The latter, usually referred to as “aliens”, were given considerable privileges under the covenant between God and Israel.</p>\n<h2>Israel's attitude to the Gentiles as outsiders</h2>\n<h3>The nations as outsiders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:8\">NEH 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:1\">PSA 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:10\">PSA 46:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:35\">PSA 106:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:8\">HOS 7:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:17\">JOL 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>The conversion of the Gentiles foretold</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:3\">ISA 60:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:18\">GEN 22:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:27\">PSA 22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:2\">ISA 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:23\">HOS 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's mission to the Gentiles was fulfilled in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:47\">ACT 13:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:6\">ISA 49:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:32\">LUK 2:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:28\">ACT 28:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:11\">ROM 11:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:6\">EPH 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ calls both Jew and Gentile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:47-Acts13:48\">ACT 13:47–13:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:24-Rom9:26\">ROM 9:24–9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:24\">1CO 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:17\">2TI 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's attitude to aliens as outsiders</h2>\n<h3>Aliens are to be treated as members of the people of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:9\">EXO 23:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:9-Deut29:15\">DEU 29:9–29:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:12\">DEU 31:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:33-Josh8:35\">JOS 8:33–8:35</a></p>\n<h3>Aliens are protected by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:9\">PSA 146:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Aliens must not be oppressed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:3\">JER 22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:2-Jer7:7\">JER 7:2–7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:29\">EZK 22:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:9-Zech7:10\">ZEC 7:9–7:10</a></p>\n<h3>Aliens may share in Israel's worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:17-Exod12:20\">EXO 12:17–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:43-Exod12:49\">EXO 12:43–12:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:17-Lev22:19\">LEV 22:17–22:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:13-Deut16:15\">DEU 16:13–16:15</a></p>\n<h2>The Samaritans as outsiders in Israel in NT times</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:9\">JHN 4:9</a></strong> <em>By including Samaritans in his ministry, Jesus Christ demonstrated his concern for those who were treated as outsiders by society.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:33\">LUK 10:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:16\">LUK 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:7\">JHN 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are compared to aliens in the world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The witness of believers to outsiders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:5\">COL 4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:11\">MRK 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:12-1Cor5:13\">1CO 5:12–5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:11-1Thess4:12\">1TH 4:11–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:7</a></p>",
